2.1 Requirements
================

mu/mu4e are known to work on a wide variety of Unix- and Unix-like
systems, including many Linux distributions, MacOS and FreeBSD. `emacs'
23 or 24 is required, as well as Xapian(1) and GMime(2).

   mu has optional support the Guile 2.x (Scheme) programming language.
There are also some GUI-tools, which require GTK+ and Webkit; either
the GTK+2 or GTK+3-versions.

   If you intend to compile it yourself, you need to have the typical
development tools, such as C and C++ compilers (both `gcc' and `clang'
should work), GNU Autotools and `make', and (if you use them) the
development packages for GTK+, Webkit and Guile.

   ---------- Footnotes ----------

   (1) `http://xapian.org/'

   (2) `http://spruce.sourceforge.net/gmime/'


